and strategic simulation, but there is quite a bit of cooperation between both industries...<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=largthemiserable>Largthemiserable</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 823<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/29/03 6:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=910.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video games to combat terrorism</span><hr size=1> You'd be shocked what a bunch of teens and twenty-year olds can figure out strategy-wise if you give them a video game (like, say, Counterstrike, or a flight sim). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wenin>Wenin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read porn more<BR>
than I play EQ...</span><br>  Posts: 2056<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/29/03 7:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=910.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video games to combat terrorism</span><hr size=1> Problem with video game strategy games vs Real Life..... video games work with hard figures.... real life has to much variation. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6094" target="top">Wenin Huirunda</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
&quot;You can believe whatever you wish. Just realize that you are wrong. Even if you don't realize it you are still wrong. The end.&quot; - Wise Man</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=largthemiserable>Largthemiserable</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 824<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/29/03 8:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=910.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video games to combat terrorism</span><hr size=1> Perhaps the next generation of video games will be more adaptive to variables?  From physical performance of the person holding the gun, to mechanical variables (you never get a gun jam in Counterstrike, or a dud grenade...), to adaptive terrain, there are all kinds of improvements that can be made in even the best of today's video games.  And the better the sim, the better the real-life performance (no matter if the sim is a video game or a practice combat field). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enzoblueksies>Enzo Blueksies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 499<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/30/03 7:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=910.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video games to combat terrorism</span><hr size=1> For best realism I like Operation Flaspoint.  Real aiming, like down the barrel, real grenade throwing physics etc.  And if you get shot it really hurts.  Not full realism for fun's sake - usually you can take 4-5 bullets before dead - but alot closer.  Your aim gets shaky and you can't stand after 2-3 bullets, it gets really intense.<br>
<br>
As far as a learning tool, it blows America's Army away imo.  Mostly because you can make your own maps and adjust every detail.  There's also about 30 plus fully functional vehicles, you can do parachute drops, door gunner, tank commander, whole bunch of stuff.<br>
<br>
Only game I've played yet where real life combat training translated into the game.  We had a couple of combat veterans in our clan and they were always the last to die.  It was interesting because if we got stuck in death-loop on a certain mission, one of them would step up and say &quot;Ok, let's try this my way, follow me&quot; and we'd live.  Wild stuff. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:grey;font-family:century gothic;font-size:xx-small;">People demand freedom of speech as a compensation<br>
