</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wenin>Wenin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read porn more<BR>
than I play EQ...</span><br>  Posts: 2057<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/30/03 7:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=910.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video games to combat terrorism</span><hr size=1> The AI in Operation Flashpoint isn't advanced enough.  The enemy soldiers are predictable, to the point that I made it a habit of killing every single one of them in each map.  I especially loved that mission where you ambushed the tank convoy on the road, and then had to take out the village of troops. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6094" target="top">Wenin Huirunda</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
&quot;You can believe whatever you wish. Just realize that you are wrong. Even if you don't realize it you are still wrong. The end.&quot; - Wise Man</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enzoblueksies>Enzo Blueksies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 500<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/30/03 9:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=910.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Video games to combat terrorism</span><hr size=1> True true when you raise the AI skill level in Flashpoint they just get super accurate aim,(to the point where an officer can headshot you from 300 yards, lol), they don't get smarter.  But some guys get pretty creative with the mapmaking and can fake some really good ai.  That's the fun part kicking in though, in RL i'd get maybe 1 kill in a 2 year war tour and count myself lucky it wasn't me.  In Flashpoint I can get 10-40 kills in one mission :P<br>
<br>
You'd think PvP would be the way to go, but unles you've got a really comprehensive map with objectives etc, it's just same 'ol fragfest.  Best combat sim on the market I still think, been playing for years.  Flashpoint 2 won't come out until 2005 they say so mod community goes nuts.  It's fun.<br>
